</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="327" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,786,1634,1754]" pageId="4" pageNumber="327">
<emphasis box="[174,317,1698,1722]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="327">Distribution.</emphasis>
– Mostly neotropical, but with a smaller number of species in 
<collectingCountry box="[363,491,1730,1754]" name="Madagascar" pageId="4" pageNumber="327">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and Africa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="327" type="multiple">
<paragraph blockId="4.[174,711,1793,1818]" box="[174,711,1793,1818]" pageId="4" pageNumber="327">
<emphasis box="[174,512,1794,1818]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="327">
Number of species in 
<collectingCountry box="[383,508,1794,1818]" name="Madagascar" pageId="4" pageNumber="327">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
– 35 (all endemic)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[174,648,1858,1882]" box="[174,648,1858,1882]" pageId="4" pageNumber="327">
<emphasis box="[174,349,1858,1882]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="327">Recent literature.</emphasis>
– 
<bibRefCitation author="VAN DER WERFF, H." box="[375,644,1858,1882]" pageId="4" pageNumber="327" pagination="235 - 279" refId="ref4676" refString="VAN DER WERFF, H. (2013 b). A revision of the genus Ocotea Aubl. (Lauraceae) in Madagascar and the Comoro Islands. Adansonia ser. 3, 35: 235 - 279." type="journal article" year="2013">VAN DER WERFF (2013b)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="327" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[824,1475,279,527]" pageId="4" pageNumber="327">
<emphasis box="[862,917,280,303]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="327">Notes</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName box="[947,1014,279,302]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="4" pageNumber="327" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[947,1014,279,302]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="327">Ocotea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily recognized in 
<collectingCountry box="[1256,1384,279,303]" name="Madagascar" pageId="4" pageNumber="327">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
. It is the only genus which has flowers with quadrilocular stamens and fruits seated in a cupule. Some of its species have domatia, tufts of hairs or pits in the axils of some of the secondary veins. Domatia do not occur in species of the other genera in 
<collectingCountry name="Madagascar" pageId="4" pageNumber="327">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and sterile specimens with domatia can be assigned with confidence to 
<taxonomicName box="[1029,1096,471,494]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="4" pageNumber="327" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1029,1096,471,494]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="327">Ocotea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Most species have alternate leaves, but a few have opposite or subopposite leaves.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
